<br>
The bazaar seems to bring out the greedy nature in people.   Honestly, who would pay 25pp for a Silver Necklace with no benefits at all (stats, AC, HPs, effects, etc) and only sells to a vendor for 2pp?   There were 3 different vendors selling this item yesterday.<br>
<br>
<br>
Mendel<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bregaladlow>Bregalad LoW</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Enchanter Realm Master</span><br>  Posts: 156<br> <font color=#330000>(9/4/03 11:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=310.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Price gouging for lev 16 pages?</span><hr size=1> Well, today EQ has such a proliferation of quests, recipes, etc, that some people get an item drop and have no idea what it's for.  Especially those without Allakhazam premium.  So, someone reasons that maybe this silver necklace is for some quest, and desides to put it out on bazaar for 25pp, and see if it sells.  Then a couple other people who got a Silver Necklace, and don't know its use, check bazaar, and see it for 25pp.   So they figure they'll stick theirs in at that price too.  And now you got a chain reaction.  Those Silver necklaces are gonna sit in people's satchels till their owners need the space for other stuff.   <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Bregalad Alcarin</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, High Elf Phantasmist, Xev &lt;Legends of Westwood&gt;<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.webspan.net/~scorpio/graph/mezzed.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zasrasis>Zasrasis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#330000>(9/5/03 6:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=310.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Price gouging for lev 16 pages?</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the advice on where to look. EK is a great idea, haven't tried there yet. I'm sorry to say that it appears people on this server are just plain greedy or stupid. I saw another guy selling pg 26 today, one half for 200pp. The 3000pp guy is still there Lol. It's crazy considering I am likely to fail combining them a couple times. <br>
<br>
I have noticed everything on Quellious is more expensive then my old server Xegony. I realize Xegony is one of the oldest, original servers so the economy is different but this is absurd.<br>
<br>
This research stuff is nonsense IMO. My Druid, Bard, BL, and Shaman just go buy their spells and then continue doing fun things. Enchanters are forced into tedious activities like this. (I guess Mages and Wizards are too.) I have already wasted at least 12 hours the last week looking for these stupid pages on NPC venders and in the bazaar.<br>
